Re: auto backing up of wallet.dat

Bitcointalk

2010-08-26 00:57:40 UTC - [11]Original Post

   I started posting in the other topic but Iʼll repeat here, this thread
   seems more specific to the topic.
   The main backup improvement will be a pre-generated pool of keys and a
   rescan at load to scrape missed transactions from the block history.
   Then a backup will last forward for a long time.
   I was starting to post the same idea you said nelisky.
   How about a json-rpc command that locks the wallet, flushes it, copies
   wallet.dat to a location you specified, then unlocks it?  That would be
   a smaller project than the pooled keys, so maybe it could be done
   first.
   Whatʼs the simplest portable way to copy a file?  Is there something in
   Boost?
   What should it be named?  maybe:
   backupwallet <destination>
